**Summary of what was implemented:**

Implemented `hive merge [agents...]` — an orchestrated rebase-and-push command with full conflict handling.

**Files changed:**
- `src/commands/merge.ts` (new) — the merge command implementation
- `src/index.ts` — registered `registerMergeCommand`

**Features implemented per acceptance criteria:**
- `hive merge [agents...]` registered in `src/index.ts`, implemented in `src/commands/merge.ts`
- No args: merges all agents with commits ahead of main, alphabetically sorted
- With args: merges only specified agents in given order
- Pre-merge checks: verifies worktree is clean, counts commits ahead, skips agents with no new commits
- Per-agent sequence: fetch → rebase onto origin/main → push to main (fast-forward)
- On conflict: stops, prints conflict files, offers resolution instructions (cd to worktree, fix, `git rebase --continue`, then `hive merge --continue`)
- `--dry-run` shows what would be merged without doing it
- `--continue` resumes after a manually resolved conflict (state persisted in `.hive/state/merge-state.json`)
- Summary printed at the end with per-agent results (merged/skipped/conflict/failed)

**Quality gates:** All pass — typecheck, 122 tests, build.
